A tragic incident unfolded as an Adam Air plane crashed in Indonesia's mountainous region, claiming the lives of at least 90 individuals.
Among the passengers were three Americans, identified as Scott Jackson, Stephanie, and Lindsay.
The rescue operation faced delays, prompting criticism from officials.
The cause of the crash remains unknown, with reports citing adverse weather conditions.
Indonesian President expressed deep concern over the recent air disaster and ferry sinking incidents.
The nation mourns the loss of lives as rescue teams work tirelessly to recover bodies and investigate the tragic event.
